Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Zoned RU4 Primary Production Small Lots

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE, as the exclusive listing agent, is pleased to present a significant landbank opportunity at 11 Neville Road, Schofields to the market. Located in the rapidly growing suburb of Schofields, the subject block sits on a sizable 45,020sqm* (11.2 acres*) zoned RU4 Primary Production Small Lots. This rare land banking opportunity benefits from flexible planning controls and allows investors and developers the opportunity to enter into the North West Growth area.

The subject site sits on the corner of Carnarvon Road and Neville Road and is located in proximity to various transport offerings such as the newly installed and highly praised Sydney Metro Line at Tallawong.

11 Neville Road, Schofields benefits from the following key attributes:
- Sizable 45,020sqm* (11.2 acres*)
- RU4 Primary Production Small Lots Zoning
- Dual Street Frontages to Neville Road and Carnarvon Road
- Passive Gross Passing Income of $39,750* per annum
- Benefits from the North West Growth Area Plan
- Proximity to shops, public transportation options, parks, community facilities, major thoroughfares and schools

11 Neville Road, Schofields will be sold via private treaty with a price guide of $3,100,000 - $3,200,000.

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

Located in the popular and rapidly developing North West region of Sydney, this residential englobo development site in Schofields represents an outstanding opportunity to create a master planned residential estate.

The site is located in the Blacktown City Council Local Government Area at the intersection of Schofields Road and Railway Terrace. The site has a total area of 12.02 hectares* (9.92 developable hectares*) and is zoned for Medium Density Residential development.

Key information:
• Potential for apartments, townhouses and terraces
• Maximum building height of 16 metres ( 5 levels*)
• Floor Space Ratio of 1.75:1
• Walking distance to Schofields train station and local Woolworths supermarket

To view the tender document visit www.urbangrowthnsw.com.au/​etender

The invitation to Tender closes 3pm, Wednesday 19 November 2014.


*approx.
